&lt;p&gt;As Director of Client Engineering you will&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Architectural Advocacy&lt;/strong&gt;: Partner with our Staff Engineers to drive a pragmatic frontend strategy. You will take a hands-on approach to identifying and resolving bottlenecks in our large-scale monorepo workflows, ensuring the codebase remains sustainable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Stewardship &amp;amp; Efficiency&lt;/strong&gt;: Advocate for the technical solutions that make the most sense for Tide’s business goals. You will evaluate our current stack and workforce model to ensure we are maximising engineering leverage without sacrificing the right tool for the job.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Virtualisation &amp;amp; Observability&lt;/strong&gt;: Advocate for systems that provide stakeholders globally with full visibility into the product experience across all configurations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Delivery Excellence&lt;/strong&gt;: Be responsible for the delivery of a modern Release Engineering model. You will ensure your teams implement a comprehensive automation strategy that prioritises high-frequency, predictable deployment cycles.&lt;/li&gt;
